===Verb===
{{en-verb|takes a bow|taking a bow|took a bow|taken a bow}}

# To [[bow]] (gesture of deference).
# {{lb|en|idiomatic}} To [[accept]] [[praise]], as [[performer]]s in a [[theater]] at the [[end]] of their [[act]].
# {{lb|en|idiomatic}} To [[end]] a [[performance]]; to [[leave]].
# {{lb|en|idiomatic|sarcasm}} To take [[credit]] or [[blame]] for a particular outcome or circumstance.
#: ''The years we spent together were the worst years of of my life. You can '''take a bow'''.''

